title: U-17 World Cup: Paraguay thumps Syria 4-1
text:
U-17 World Cup: Paraguay thumps Syria 4-1
Paraguay had no trouble on Monday in Group F play at the U-17 WC, thumping Syria 4-1.
The goals for the Paraguayans were scored by midfielder Jorge Morel at 30 minutes, striker Julio Villalba (34), midfielder Josue Colman (65) and Carlos Ferreira (90), while Syria got their lone goal through Anas Alaji (62). The amtch was played in the Chinquihue stadium.
The Paraguayan squad was clearly superior, showing their usual strength and speed, but also using the long-range shot to put their opponent off balance.
Also in Group F play, France thrashed New Zealand 6-1.
Text and photo: AFP
Edition: conmebol.com
